{
  "article_id": "TheColdSpringRecorder1930",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The story of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman \"Robinson Crusoe\"",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who lived alone, on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an Island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for 20 long years is told by ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. Roy L. Moodie",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "rmo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who has been delving into the records of old native life in the region of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Monica, Calif",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "., in his study of prehistoric diseases in ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "America",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "co_usa",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The feminine Crusoe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been a member of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a small group of Indians",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "which lived on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", off the ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "coast, about 100 years ago.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The Spanish fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "misfats",
          "ndur",
          "aji"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "persuaded "
      },
      {
        "text": "the group",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to leave "
      },
      {
        "text": "their lonely island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and find better protection at the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". But "
      },
      {
        "text": "this woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "refused to come. All alone she demonstrated her self-sufficiency in the world by making her home of whale ribs and brush, and by living off the abundant fish, abalones, birds, seals and some plant products. She made her clothing of bird skins. "
      },
      {
        "text": "When at last she was brought to ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mission",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "she died within six weeks.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The island",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "possesses many relics of aboriginal life, but none so romantic as the record of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last woman",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Doctor Moodie",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "rmo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "said.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "—Kansas City Star's Science Service."
      }
    ]
  ]
}